div.p: Sometimes it can be quite intense, you have to put a lot of hours into what you do and that requires sacrifices, I make social sacrifices almost
but it’s not catastrophic I just can’t go out one night or I can’t make my football training day or something along those lines
so you know you’ve got to prioritise and meeting your deadlines is the number one priority when you’re studying at least and when you’re
working at the Council you’ve got to make sure you’ve done the job you’ve said you’re going to do, you’ve got to fulfil your commitments.
